Philip Kgosana passed away at a Pretoria hospital last week after a short illness. CAPE TOWN - Former Pan Africanist Congress (PAC) leader Philip Kgosana is being laid to rest.Kgosana died last week at the age of 80 after a short illness.In 1960, he led more than 30,000 anti-pass law protestors.President Jacob Zuma has declared a special provincial funeral for the veteran.WATCH: Philip Kgosana's funeral service